// nodule: std.core.error_scaffold
// `std.core::error_scaffold` ‚Äî the shared, non-coupling scaffold for stdlib error
// types (M-535, E5-1; DN-17 ¬ß2.4/¬ß4 P3).
//
// # What this is (and deliberately is *not*)
// Every `mycelium-std-*` crate hand-rolls, per error type, the *same three mechanical
// pieces*: `#[derive(Debug, ‚Ä¶)]`, an `impl std::error::Error` marker (occasionally with a
// `source()` delegate), and a `*_is_std_error` compile-time test. DN-17 ¬ß2.4 measured
// ~600 LOC of this `Display`/`Error`/test boilerplate as structurally repeated. This
// module factors out **only the mechanical part**:
//
// - [`StdError`] ‚Äî a *marker* super-trait (`Debug + Display + std::error::Error`) that
//   *names* the per-op never-silent / EXPLAIN contract (RFC-0016 ¬ß4.1 C1/C3) so "this
//   value is an honest stdlib error" is inspectable and bound-checkable, with a blanket
//   impl so no type opts in by hand.
// - [`impl_std_error!`](crate::impl_std_error) ‚Äî a tiny declarative macro that emits the boilerplate
//   `impl std::error::Error for T {}` (optionally with a `source()` arm), leaving the
//   **hand-written, domain-specific `Display` message in the caller** ‚Äî untouched.
// - `assert_is_std_error` / `assert_display_contains` ‚Äî the test helpers DN-17 ¬ß4
//   blesses as the *safe* consolidation (the `*_is_std_error` + `*_display_includes_*`
//   duplication), gated behind `#[cfg(any(test, feature = "test-support"))]` (so they are
//   absent ‚Äî and these names unlinkable ‚Äî in a default doc build).
//
// ## What it does NOT do (VR-5 / DN-17 ¬ß5 ‚Äî non-coupling by construction)
// It never generates, alters, or inspects a `Display` *message*; never adds, removes, or
// renames an error variant; never changes a `#[derive]`; and never touches a per-module
// guarantee tag or the per-module guarantee matrix (RFC-0016 ¬ß4.5 ‚Äî intentionally
// per-module, DN-17 ¬ß3). A refactor through this scaffold is **behaviour-preserving**: the
// only code it emits is the empty `Error` marker and an optional `source()` delegate, both
// of which are byte-identical everywhere they appear today. The per-module *honesty
// contracts stay decoupled* ‚Äî this is the line DN-17 ¬ß5 draws, and the scaffold respects it.
//
// # Guarantee tag
// **`Exact`** ‚Äî the scaffold is pure, total, allocation-free glue: [`StdError`] is a marker
// with a trivial blanket impl, [`impl_std_error!`](crate::impl_std_error) expands to the exact trait impl the
// caller would otherwise write, and the assert helpers are total predicates over a borrowed
// error. No approximation, no selection, no representation choice is introduced (C5: it adds
// no trusted code ‚Äî it consumes `std::error::Error`).
//
// # Grounding
// DN-17 ¬ß2.4 (the survey), ¬ß4 P3 (test-helper = safe; macro = post-ratification), ¬ß5 (the
// non-coupling caveat); RFC-0016 ¬ß4.1 C1 (never-silent), C3 (EXPLAIN / no black box), C5
// (above the kernel); G2 (never-silent); VR-5 (a refactor never changes a guarantee).
// @summary: best-effort transpilation via mycelium-transpile (M-873). Declared,
// unvalidated ‚Äî no Mycelium parser/typechecker confirms this output; see the
// accompanying .gap.json for every construct this pass could not express.
nodule std.core.error_scaffold;


